(1)
East 134th Street, north side, west from Southern Boulevard. These buildings extending for two long blocks to Brook Ave., were later razed to make way for the approach to the Triborough Bridge.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A detail of the same, at the N.W. corner of Southern Boulevard. These bear Nos. 633 to 639 (left to right). On the extreme right is part of a large 6-story apartment house bearing Nos. 133 to 151
Southern Boulevard.

P. L. Sperr.
